<p>Short and sweet application. On submitting the form a, b values are passed to self(same page) using GET method. On reload the JS fetches values of a &amp; b from URL using getUrlParameter Method and computes there sum.</p>
<div class="row">
	<form role="form" name="SumCalculator" class="col-md-6">
		<p><label for="a">Enter value of A:</label><input id="a" class="form-control" type="number" name="a" placeholder="Enter a number" /></p>
		<p><label for="b">Enter value of B:</label><input id="b" class="form-control" type="number" name="b" placeholder="Enter a number" /></p>
		<p><input class="btn btn-info" type="submit" Value="ADD"/></p>
		<h4 class="mt-2">Output (A+B): <span id="output"></span></h4>
	</form>
</div>
<hr/>
<h3>Code</h3>
<GithubCodeHighlighter id="code-js" program="getUrlParameter.js" repo="shivajivarma/codebase-js" language="javascript" />

```javascript
$(document).ready(function(){
	var a = getUrlParameter("a");
	var b = getUrlParameter("b");
	if(a!="" && b!=""){
		if($.isNumeric(a) && $.isNumeric(b)){
			$("#output").html(+a + +b);
		}
		else  $("#output").html("Enter only numbers.");
	}
	else $("#output").html("Please fill the input and hit add button.");
});
```

